		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Thats what I thought.  It would seem that the mapper would need both the capabilities of the MMC1 and MMC3 chips, for Tetris and Nintendo World Cup, respectively.  Unless Nintendo modified the SMB and Tetris to use the MMC3 registers.  
<br />
<br />Nintendo's practice is to use glop tops when it produces NES carts designed to be bundled with its systems.  SMB + DK, SMB + DK + WCTM, SSV + NWC all use glop tops, so he would have to have used something like CopyNES or Doctor PC to dump the game.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
